meta.@content: Manually derived terrain and bathymetry offshore Ship Island, MS.
Scripts by Don Brutzman; Scene and Data Jeffrey Weekley
An experimental version of X3D JSON encoding is used for this scene.  Status online at http://www.web3d.org/wiki/index.php/X3D_JSON_Encoding

ExternProtoDeclare.@appinfo: ViewPositionOrientation provides provides console output of local position and orientation as user navigates

field.@appinfo: Whether or not ViewPositionOrientation sends output to console.
Output internal trace messages for debugging this node - developer use only can be ignored.
Ability to turn output tracing on/off at runtime.

-children.#comment: Approximated Terrain transcribed in Feet and translated to meters (1m = 39.3", 39.3" / 12" = 3.275).
Simple ElevationGrid, not georeferenced to latitude/longitude
inputUnits are 'feet' or 'meters' - heightValuesOutput is always in meters.

#sourceText: heightValuesHold = new MFFloat (0); // grows to fit as values are appended
// this depth band defined to match fathoms to 60 feet, then 10' increments, doesn't match MEDAL
colorValuesOutput = new MFColor (); // array gets dynamically expanded
